com.softwareag.natural.mapconverter

Interface IAreaHeaderHandler

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    DEFAULTAreaHeaderHandler, LiteralAreaHeaderHandler, UnderlineAreaHeaderHandler

    public interface IAreaHeaderHandler
    Interface to be implemented by area header handlers is to identify grid headers from the extended map extract.

    The extended map extract is passed to the area header handler. The area header handler can add grid headers and do all kind of modifications like removing rows and columns in the passed MapxmlPage object.
    Version:
    $Revision: 1.1.4.3 $
    Author:
    zim

    • Method Detail

      • handleHeaders

        void handleHeaders(MapxmlPage mapxmlPage)
        Area header heandlers must implement this interface. The method is invoked after loading the map extract into a mapxmlPage and identifying grid and sequence areas. The area header handler usually retrieves the grid areas and adds GridHeader objects correspondingly.
        Parameters:
        mapxmlPage - the extended map extract containing the grid areas
